Global Differential Spandex Fiber market size was valued at USD 1.928 billion in 2026. The market is projected to reach USD 3.166 billion by 2034, exhibiting a CAGR of 7.5% during the forecast period.
Differential Spandex Fiber refers to an elastic fiber engineered with distinct structural properties that deliver superior stretch‑and‑recovery performance compared with conventional spandex (Lycra/Elastane). It is produced from polyurethane polymers and is prized for its high elasticity, durability, and ability to retain shape under repeated stress.
