Competitive Landscape
Hyosung Corporation dominates the market with a diversified portfolio encompassing high‑performance elastomers, chlorine‑resistant grades, and specialty blends. Leveraging a strong R&D network across South Korea and China, Hyosung secures large‑volume contracts for apparel and medical textiles.
Zhejiang Huafon Spandex, Huahai Group, and Highsun Group enhance their offerings with chlorine‑resistant and easy‑to‑dye variants, targeting the apparel and outdoor‑wear markets. Xinxiang Bailu Chemical Fiber and Jiangsu Shuangliang Spandex focus on cost‑effective production for domestic Chinese demand, while Taekwang Industrial and TK Chemical Corporation maintain robust distribution in Southeast Asia.
Emerging innovators such as Xiamen Lilong Spandex and Yantai Tayho Advanced Materials are investing in bio‑based elastomers, signaling a shift toward sustainable production. Collectively, these players maintain market dynamism through incremental innovation and regional diversification.
